      "span_text": "It is straight-forward to prove that a group is AC(n) for some n ≥ 2 if and only if it is AC(2). (The same cannot be said of P (2) and K  .) The proof of Theorem 1 can be generalised to show that the bounds also apply to AC(n), P (n) and K(n) groups (n ≥ 2)."
